# Cursor AI Rules for Dhanak Trinket E-commerce Platform

## Project Overview
You're working on Dhanak Trinket - an ethnic finds e-commerce platform with .NET Core backend, Next.js frontend, and Azure cloud services.

## Technology Stack
- Backend: ASP.NET Core 8.0 Web API
- Frontend: Next.js 14+ with TypeScript  
- Database: Azure SQL Database
- Storage: Azure Blob Storage
- Cloud: Azure App Service + Static Web Apps

## Code Style Rules

### C# (.NET Core)
- Use PascalCase for public members, camelCase for private fields
- Always use async/await for database operations
- Prefer LINQ methods over traditional loops
- Use nullable reference types consistently
- Implement proper error handling with Result patterns

### TypeScript/React
- No 'any' types - use proper type definitions
- Prefer functional components with hooks
- Use Tailwind CSS classes for styling
- Always handle loading and error states
- Use Next.js Image component for product photos

### Database
- Use Entity Framework Core with code-first migrations
- Add audit fields (CreatedAt, UpdatedAt) to all entities
- Implement soft deletes for important data
- Use proper navigation properties for relationships

## File Structure Conventions
```
/backend
  /JewelryHaven.Api - Controllers and API configuration
  /JewelryHaven.Core - Domain models and business logic
  /JewelryHaven.Infrastructure - Data access and external services

/frontend  
  /components - Reusable UI components
  /pages - Next.js page components
  /services - API communication logic
  /types - TypeScript type definitions
```

## Business Rules
- All jewelry products must have at least one image
- Stock status updates should be real-time
- Mobile-first responsive design is mandatory  
- Product likes don't require user authentication (for now)
- SEO optimization is critical for product discovery

## API Patterns
- Use standardized response format with success/error structure
- Implement proper HTTP status codes
- Follow RESTful naming conventions
- Add pagination to list endpoints
- Include filtering and search capabilities

## Performance Guidelines
- Use Azure CDN for image delivery
- Implement database query optimization
- Add caching for frequently accessed data
- Optimize images for different screen sizes
- Use lazy loading for product listings

## Security Rules
- Validate all inputs server-side
- Use parameterized queries to prevent SQL injection
- Implement proper CORS configuration
- Store sensitive configuration in Azure Key Vault
- Plan for future authentication integration

## Testing Requirements
- Write unit tests for business logic
- Create integration tests for API endpoints
- Test mobile responsiveness
- Validate image loading performance
- Test error handling scenarios

Remember: This is a jewelry business focusing on beautiful product presentation and excellent user experience. Always consider the visual and mobile aspects when suggesting code changes.